# Normalize line endings: store text as LF in the repo, regardless of each
# contributor's core.autocrlf setting. This makes git's diff/status consistent
# across environments (e.g. Git-for-Windows with autocrlf=true vs. a Linux/CI
# checkout with autocrlf unset), so a CRLF working tree no longer shows every
# file as "modified". Working-tree endings are still platform-native on checkout.
* text=auto

# Treat all image/binary files as binary — no line ending transforms
*.webp  binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.png   binary
*.gif   binary
*.ico   binary
*.svg   binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf   binary
*.eot   binary
*.pdf   binary
